American rock band Marilyn Manson was originally called Marilyn Manson and the Spooky Kids before being renamed in 1992.

Mark Daniel Ronson (born 4 September 1975) is a British-American, internationally renowned DJ and Academy-Award-winning, multi-Grammy-Award-winning and Golden Globe-winning songwriter and record producer from London, England.He is best known for his collaborations with artists such as Amy Winehouse, Adele, Lady Gaga, Lily Allen, Robbie Williams, Miley Cyrus, and Bruno Mars.

Maroon 5 is an American pop rock band. They were originally formed in 1994 as Kara’s Flowers while they were still attending high school. They signed to Reprise Records and released an album, The Fourth World, in 1997. After a mediocre response to the album, the band parted with their record label and attended college, but in 2001, the band regrouped, added James Valentine to the lineup, and pursued a new direction under the name Maroon 5.Their first big hit came in the form of “Harder to Breathe,” the edgier lead single from their debut, Songs About Jane. The continued success of that song and other singles “This Love,” “She Will Be Loved,” and “Sunday Morning” cemented the quintet as a pop-rock band to keep an eye out for.However, for their second album, It Won’t Be Soon Before Long, they switched to ambing up on slick pop production—and it worked for them. Lead single “Makes Me Wonder” jumped 63 places in one week to reach number one, becoming their first ever #1 single.With the releases of Hands All Over, Overexposed, and V, the group has been slowly growing poppier yet keeping their appeal. In fact, after the #14 peak of their 2010 single “Misery,” they hit the top ten with every single one of their singles until 2015’s “This Summer’s Gonna Hurt.”Their tried-and-true formula of songs that blur the line between love and hooking up has kept all of their fans from the early 2000s and made new ones far into the 2010s.

Growing up in New Jersey, Luke Terkovich (Abstract) was involved with music at an early age. Learning how to play piano, electric guitar, and the drums were Luke’s first involvement with music — and he did it all before 6th grade. With a move across the country from New Jersey to Wyoming, the distance between learning and playing new instruments got larger. It wasn’t until several years later that Luke began to experiment with freestyling during his high school years spent at Jackson Hole High, where he fell in love with rap.Today, Abstract has grown to become a successful independent artist, consistently averaging over 500,000 monthly listeners on Spotify.Abstract is the head of “A Team Worldwide,” often referred to as “ATWW.” The collective consists of 5 musicians from 4 different countries. Producer-duo Drumma Battalion of Norway (now known as Dio Mudara), Blulake of Sweden, Cryo Music of Scotland, and Abstract himself of the United States. Over the years, ATWW has grown not just to refer to Abstract’s team, but also to refer to Abstract’s fans.Abstract is most well-known for his 2015 track “Neverland” a remix of Ruth B’s “Lost Boy.” As of Feb 2022, the song has amassed over 150M views across multiple uploads on YouTube.In 2016, Abstract created his clothing and accessories brand Moon Five Two. The brand is named after a fictional planet, created by Abstract, which is the focus of his 2018 multimedia experience Super Human, a 19-track long project accompanied by its own film. The Super Human film can be viewed below on YouTube.https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G6tWttQWlIwThe planet Moon 52 stands as a metaphor for our always evolving destination as human beings. A destination defined differently in every man and woman’s mind. Our quest for our passion, our search for ourselves, our journey to purpose.

Two Friends is a Los Angeles-based duo of Matt Halper and Eli Sones. They met in high school and began producing music together, with Halper contributing his guitar, choir, and music theory experience and Sones contributing his hip-hop DJing experience. They continued to record together even though they attended different colleges, with Sones attending Vanderbilt University in Nashville and Halper attending Stanford University in Palo Alto, California.In 2013, they released their debut EP, [You (Me)], featuring the songs “Feel Me” with Priyanka Atreya and “Your Song” with I Am Lightyear. A year later, they released a pair of collaborations with Breach the Summit. The two then graduated from college in 2015 and released the singles “Forever” and “Overdose” in 2016. A year later, they released their sophomore EP, [Out of Love], with support from Spinnin' Records. This EP featured the hits “Emily,” “While We’re Dreaming,” and “Just a Kid.” Following this, the duo released various remixes for artists such as Charlie Puth, Dua Lipa, and many others, as well as other singles and collaborations.In 2021, they released their third EP, Useless, featuring the songs “This Will Be My Year” with Point North and the title track with Emily Vaughn. Today, they continue to release new music, notably “Love Love,” “Life’s Too Short,” and many others. They have become well-known for their bright, upbeat anthems, similar to those of Jonas Blue, Louis the Child, and Autograf. Their high-profile remixes for artists like Lana Del Ray and others have established them as one of the best in the EDM music industry.In summary, Two Friends is a talented duo who have made a name for themselves in the EDM music industry. They are known for their bright, upbeat anthems and their high-profile remixes.

Ciara Princess Wilson (born October 25, 1985) is an American singer, songwriter, producer, dancer, choreographer, actress & fashion model.She began her career in 2001 in Atlanta in girl group Hearsay, after writing songs for the group she was discovered by producers L.A. Reid and Tricky Stewart, who got her songwriting placements for Blu Cantrell, Fantasia, Keri Hilson and Zena McNally.In 2013, Reid signed her as an artist to his label LaFace alongside Jazze Pha’s label Sho'Nuff to release her debut album Goodies.In 2018, she left LA Reid; now at Epic Records, and signed a new deal with Warner Bros, as well as launching her own label imprint Beauty Marks Ent.She is married to Russell Wilson and has two children, Future and Sienna.

Terence Edward Parsons, better known as Matt Monro, (1 December 1930 – 7 February 1985) was an English singer who became one of the most popular entertainers on the international music scene throughout the 1950s and 1970s.Some of his major hits include “Portrait of My Love”, “My Kind of Girl”, “Softly As I Leave You” and “Walk Away”. Many of his songs were produced by George Martin, who also worked extensively with The Beatles.Monro’s popularity was bolstered in 1963 when he provided the title song for the James Bond film From Russia with Love, with his song of the same name. His songs “Born Free” and “On Days Like These” were also recorded for the screen, featuring in Born Free and The Italian Job respectively.

Marvel’s Daredevil, or simply Daredevil, is a Netflix TV series created by Drew Goddard. Based on the Marvel Comics character of the same name (created by Stan Lee and Jack Kirby in 1964), it follows the journey of Matt Murdock, a lawyer who became blind in his youth and gained super enhanced senses.The series is the first of four Marvel Studios Netflix TV series (Jessica Jones, Luke Cage and Iron Fist), which culminated in a mini-series called The Defenders. All of these shows are within the Marvel Cinematic Universe (or MCU).

Matt Redman is is an English Christian worship leader, singer, songwriter and author from Chorleywood.He’s married to Beth and they have five children. They are currently based on the south coast of England, near Brighton.Matt has been a full-time worship leader since the age of 20 and this journey has taken him to countries such as South Africa, Japan, India, Australia, Germany and the Czech RepublicAlong the way he has sung in venues such as the Angels baseball stadium, both old and new Wembley stadiums, St Paul’s Cathedral and the Royal Albert Hall. He has been involved in a number of events for the Passion Conferences and worked with Hillsong London.He co-wrote the 2005 Dove Award-winning “Blessed Be Your Name” (Worship Song of the Year) and the Grammy Award nominated “Our God”.The single of “10,000 Reasons (Bless the Lord)”, co-written with Jonas Myrin,  spent 16 weeks at the top spot on Christian Radio and remained No. 1 on the Billboard Christian Songs Chart for 13 weeks and was certified gold in the United States.As part of his achievements, Redman has won two Grammy Awards, the awards for Best Contemporary Christian Music Song and Best Gospel/Contemporary Christian Music Performance, as well as the Gospel Music Association’s Dove Award for Song of the Year.

Matt Johnson is a dynamic, classically trained pianist who received his Bachelor of Music degree in Piano Performance from Oklahoma Baptist University. As a graduate student at New England Conservatory of Music, he formally expanded his talents in the area of composition. Studying under William Thomas McKinley, he received his Master of Music degree in Jazz Studies and Composition with a Distinction in Performance.A prolific writer and performer, Matt has performed extensively in venues from Boston to Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. His music is Neo-Romantic, employing a unique blend of contemporary jazz, new age, popular and classical elements.Additionally, Matt has composed and arranged for many mediums. His choral, vocal, instrumental, handbell and piano scores are available as free PDF downloads from his site.Matt has been studying/playing the piano since the age of six…there’s a picture of him practicing on the cover of his Origins recording. His classical training has included numerous piano performance competitions and orchestral appearances.Matt is a writer member of A.S.C.A.P. and his publishing company, Dolce & Nuit Productions, is a publisher member as well.Born in Sherman, Texas, Matt currently resides in Florida. His versatility allows him to teach piano, theory and composition…play piano, organ and keyboards for both Contemporary and Traditional services at his local church…as well as accompany and adjudicate music festivals and competitions.

The Passion Conference (a.k.a. the 268 Generation, f.k.a Choice Ministries) was founded in 1997 by Louie Giglio. The annual gathering, which still continues to this day, is comprised of young adults from age 18-25.A defining feature of the conference is Passion music. The main worship leaders include Kristian Stanfill, Brett Younker, and Melodie Malone. Other artists that have had a big role in Passion’s music have been Chris Tomlin, David Crowder, Matt Redman, Christy Nockels, Jimi Cravity, Jeff Johnson, and Sean Curran (formerly of Bellarive). The band has released 20 albums, with hit songs† such as One Thing Remains, 10,000 Reasons (Bless the Lord), White Flag, The Lord Our God, Here’s My Heart, My Heart is Yours, Even So Come, Remember, and others.†Some songs were also released on some of the artists' solo albums, such as Tomlin, Crowder, and Redman.

The Republican Donald J. Trump is the 45th and 47th President of the United States of America. Aiming to “Make America Great Again,” he is notable for his legislative actions and beliefs which are often identified as conservative and right-wing.
Young Rich Republicans is a rap group from Wauconda, Illinois, consisting of Matt O'Brien and twins Matt Nolan and Drew Nolan. The trio formed in 2017.

Mazzy Star is a band formed in 1989 by Hope Sandoval (vocals) and David Roback (guitar). As of now, they have released four full-length albums: She Hangs Brightly (1990, Rough Trade), So Tonight That I Might See (1993, Capitol), Among My Swan (1996, Capitol) and Seasons Of Your Day (2013, Rhymes Of An Hour Records).Hope and David met in the mid-80s. At that time, Hope was playing in a band called Going Home (named after the Rolling Stones' song) with her friend Sylvia Gomez, while David played in the band Opal (after leaving Rain Parade) with Kendra Smith.According to Hope’s official website “Sylvia Gomez handed Kendra Smith a demo tape which was comprised of Hope Sandoval on vocals and Sylvia on guitar. David Roback offered to produce some recordings for them and they went into the studio and recorded an album that to this day is yet to be released.”In December 1987, on tour after they released their debut LP, Kendra left Opal and David asked Hope if she would be interested in replacing her. Until 1989, they continued playing as Opal, before they changed their name to Mazzy Star.In a 2009 interview, Hope recalls the first contact with David, feeling like the “luckiest person ever” after he called her, wanting to play guitar for Going Home, because she was a fan of Rain Parade.
